<div id="executive-summary" class="page-break">
  <h1>Executive Summary</h1>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>This comprehensive retirement planning analysis evaluates your financial trajectory through {{projections.milestones.length}} years of projections, 
    utilizing Monte Carlo simulation with {{formatNumber assumptions.mcRuns}} iterations to account for market volatility and economic uncertainty.</p>
    
    <div class="kpi-grid">
      {{> kpi-tile 
        value=(formatPercent projections.successRatePct)
        label="Retirement Success Probability"
        badge=(getSuccessBadge projections.successRatePct)
        badgeColor=(getSuccessBadgeColor projections.successRatePct)
        note=(concat "Based on " (formatNumber assumptions.mcRuns) " Monte Carlo simulations")
      }}
      
      {{> kpi-tile 
        value=(formatEUR finances.currentAssetsEUR)
        label="Current Assets"
        note="Starting portfolio value"
      }}
      
      {{> kpi-tile 
        value=(formatEUR finances.annualSavingsEUR)
        label="Annual Savings"
        note="Pre-retirement contribution"
      }}
      
      {{> kpi-tile 
        value=(formatEUR finances.expectedMonthlyPensionEUR)
        label="Expected Monthly Pension"
        note=(concat "Starting at age " person.pensionAge)
      }}
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="no-number">Monthly Spending Requirements</h2>
    
    <div class="spending-breakdown avoid-break">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Monthly Amount</th>
            <th>Annual Total</th>
            <th>% of Total</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Healthcare</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.health}}</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.health 12)}}</td>
            <td>{{formatPercent (getSpendingPercent spending.monthly.health spending)}}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Food & Groceries</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.food}}</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.food 12)}}</td>
            <td>{{formatPercent (getSpendingPercent spending.monthly.food spending)}}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Entertainment</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.entertainment}}</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.entertainment 12)}}</td>
            <td>{{formatPercent (getSpendingPercent spending.monthly.entertainment spending)}}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Shopping</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.shopping}}</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.shopping 12)}}</td>
            <td>{{formatPercent (getSpendingPercent spending.monthly.shopping spending)}}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Utilities</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.utilities}}</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.utilities 12)}}</td>
            <td>{{formatPercent (getSpendingPercent spending.monthly.utilities spending)}}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="font-weight: 600; border-top: 2pt solid var(--line);">
            <td>Total Monthly</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR (getTotalMonthlySpending spending)}}</td>
            <td>{{formatEUR (getTotalAnnualSpending spending)}}</td>
            <td>100%</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    
    <div class="callout callout-info">
      <div class="callout-title">Key Findings</div>
      <ul>
        <li>Your portfolio has a {{formatPercent projections.successRatePct}} probability of sustaining your retirement through age {{person.horizonAge}}</li>
        <li>Median portfolio value at retirement (age {{person.retireAge}}): {{formatEUR (getRetirementMedian projections person)}}</li>
        <li>Total annual spending requirement: {{formatEUR (getTotalAnnualSpending spending)}}</li>
        <li>Years until retirement: {{subtract person.retireAge person.currentAge}}</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>